Cerulean Slicks Flagged as Possible Seep Detections

These possible seeps' approximate ocean surface outbreak points serve as centroids for 15 square kilometer bounding boxes containing ground truth seep locations identified by researchers at Texas A&M University and Florida State University and SAR-based satellite natural seep detections found in the 2014-2020 Global Oil Slick SAR Dataset (GlobalOSD-SAR).
